  <p class="text-block justified">
    <b>About Game Scores:</b> When devising the concept for this
    project, our group wished for a method to use player
    statistics to compare performance; we envisioned a ranking
    system similar to OVR ranking in NBA 2K games. After some
    searching, we discovered a calculated statistic called
    "Game Score" conceived by basketball writer/analyst
    <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Hollinger">
      John Hollinger</a>. The stat is meant to generalize a player's performance
    in a single game, and was created to be compared on a scale
    similar to points: 20 is a good score whereas a single
    digit score represents a less productive game. Details about
    the calculation of Game Score can be found
    <a href="https://captaincalculator.com/sports/basketball/game-score-calculator/">
      here</a>. Our project automatically calculates this statistic after
    reading the data for each game. This statistic is aggregated
    across the entire team in various way in the following graphs.
  </p>
